dogecoin.text:
My problem with all of this is that Dogecoin Cash ALREADY existed as a coin, since 2019. This Dogecoin Cash, ticker $DOGEC, is a masternode capped version of Doge which has nothing to do with this crap I just wrote above.

So. yeah. Don't confuse $DOGEC with $DOG.

So if Kronos already held First Bitcoin, it makes only sense that they'd trade it freely for Dogecoin Cash, as they are propriety of the same company, and they can make use of both money they already had tied in a Coin/Token that was useless and use the Doge hype.

In February this year, their client Tipestry partnered with the Dogecoin Cash Public Benefit Coporation to create a new Defi token Dogecoin Cash, an ERC20/BEP20 token. Said corporation is legal and based in Colorado. https://t.co/7ESvdI4GxA

If anyone has read the bombastic news on Kronos, the DogeSPAC and all that. So here's what I've found.

So. The news says that they'll convert First Bitcoin, $BIT, into Dogecoin Cash, $DOG.
https://t.co/qgCDH3vE68

@BillyM2k Dogecoin Cash Foundation does not exist, but the https://t.co/7ESvdI4GxA is registered to Dogecoin Cash Public Benefit Corporation, which exists in Colorado.

@BillyM2k So, I talked with Liquid369, dev of Dogecoin Cash. He wasn't aware of the situation but found this: https://t.co/jROERSh69r
It's a DeFi token created this year, by the german company  BOTS, Inc.

@BillyM2k Yeah, I was looking into that just now as well. Looks more like a confused mis/malinformation. And the supposed "Dogecoin Cash Foundation" has literally zero entries on google. It must be the name Dogecoin Cash that is wrong here.

@BillyM2k @DeItaone If it is Dogecoin Cash, then that's a semi-known older project. If it's a new thing, then you are right.
But since the ticker says one thing, but the name says other, maybe whoever wrote it got much confused?
